properties.abstract: The big star of this hike is the diverse landscape around Arosa. From the highest point, the Hauptichopf peak, you can enjoy the splendid panorama of the Schanfigg and Rhine Valleys near Chur. Due to its convenient location, the trail is accessible from spring onwards and a popular early-season route.
properties.description:
The Arosa train station is used as the starting point for this four-hour hike. The trailhead is marked at the valley station of the Arosa  Weisshorn cable car. The first section goes over the Scheitenbden to the middle station of the Weisshorn cable car. After just 1.5 km you reach the timberline, and the Alpine panorama opens right out. The path leads across the rolling countryside with great views to the highest point of the tour, the Hauptichopf.

After a further interesting journey along the Scheidegg with superb views, walk down to the Ochsenalp inn. After refreshments in the cosy alpine refuge, you reach the Prtschalp via the Rot Tritt section. Continue between the upper and lower Prtsch lakes, above the golf course, past the Maran dairy farm, to the final highlight of the round trip, the Eichhrnliweg, and back to the railway station.

The Eichhrnliweg section is particularly popular with families. Along the way, you will come across some well-maintained fireplaces offering a welcoming respite.
